        "created_at": "2017-01-12T09:13:39.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2030679&amp;iNote=6127127\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2012 Domaine Pierre Gelin Fixin 1er Cru Clos Napoleon</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Fixin 1er Cru</em><br>\nA lovely young Burg. Good, bright ruby colour. Perfumes of raspberries, cranberries, a little blue fruit, minerals and red liquorice. Some spices and soil. On palate, crystalline, crunchy red cherries and red currants, blueberries, minerals and earth. Mid weight, nervous with energetic acidity. Some attractive austerity. Subtle grip. \u2018Great textural depth\u2019 said Andrew. Accessible now but it\u2019ll improve with 3-5 years in the cellar. <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
